006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model.xml.impl.DefaultContainerModelAssemblySupport;
009
010import java.util.List;
011import java.util.Map;
012
013import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
014
015/**
016 * Common interface for model container support classes.
017 *
018 * @param <MI>
019 *          the model instance Java type
020 * @param <NMI>
021 *          the named model instance Java type
022 * @param <FI>
023 *          the field instance Java type
024 * @param <AI>
025 *          the assembly instance Java type
026 * @param <CI>
027 *          the choice instance Java type
028 * @param <CGI>
029 *          the choice group instance Java type
030 */
031public interface IContainerModelAssemblySupport<
032    MI extends IModelInstance,
033    NMI extends INamedModelInstance,
034    FI extends IFieldInstance,
035    AI extends IAssemblyInstance,
036    CI extends IChoiceInstance,
037    CGI extends IChoiceGroupInstance> extends IContainerModelSupport<MI, NMI, FI, AI> {
038
039  /**
040   * Get an empty, immutable container.
041   *
042   * @param <MI>
043   *          the model instance Java type
044   * @param <NMI>
045   *          the named model instance Java type
046   * @param <FI>
047   *          the field instance Java type
048   * @param <AI>
049   *          the assembly instance Java type
050   * @param <CI>
051   *          the choice instance Java type
052   * @param <CGI>
053   *          the choice group instance Java type
054   * @return the empty container
055   */
056  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
057  static <
058      MI extends IModelInstance,
059      NMI extends INamedModelInstance,
060      FI extends IFieldInstance,
061      AI extends IAssemblyInstance,
062      CI extends IChoiceInstance,
063      CGI extends IChoiceGroupInstance> IContainerModelAssemblySupport<MI, NMI, FI, AI, CI, CGI> empty() {
064    return DefaultContainerModelAssemblySupport.EMPTY;
065  }
066
067  /**
068   * Get a listing of all choice instances.
069   *
070   * @return the listing
071   */
072  @NonNull
073  List<CI> getChoiceInstances();
074
075  /**
076   * Get a listing of all choice group instances.
077   *
078   * @return the listing
079   */
080  @NonNull
081  Map<String, CGI> getChoiceGroupInstanceMap();
082}
